replies.body:
Honestly, I can see how you think that. I can, especially with players these days and the people on the boards (Sometimes they make my eyes bleed with the sheer amount of blonde), but I've never had a trend of being toxic at all. I almost always logged in to find key fragments waiting for my honors. Then the one time I argue with someone who was intentionally being, let be real, toxic, I get hit with a smack that isn't anywhere close as to what I find, pleasurable. 

The reps advice is wonderful but honestly. Muting and ignoring players isn't gonna fix the problem. Cause that player can just report back and the system will find SOME reason to punish. Since at this rate, muting players will most likely be seen as a form as unsportsmanlike conduct. Cause you're ignoring your own team. We're starting to walk from the line of "Oh wells, It's a game and I can do better." to "My feelers were hurt, someone punish them.". 

Thanks for the luck, I'm just gonna take a nice long break till later in season 10. I upvoted you btw {{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
